  New subject: Rootless podman - access to volume (host directory mount) owned by different user
  
  
  Hello Geert,
  
  when you start a rootless podman container, the root user inside the
  container will be mapped to your user on the host.
  
  As all host users are member of the "share" group, maybe you could just
  keep using root inside the container? Set a sticky group ID for the shared
  volume, so that all created files are automatically owned by the "share"
  group.
  
  cheers,
  Roland
  
