  - None of the above are relevant to the problem. I have determined the source - podman does not run the same way docker does. Docker uses fuse-ovelayfs to abstract file permissions on mounted volumes whereas (rootless) podman does not. Podman maps the uid/gid in the container to uid/gid 0 on the host by default. This means when volumes are mounted from the host they appear as being owned by uid/gid 0 in the container. I'll post a solution to the problem later today.
  
  
  
