  [Bruce](https://stackoverflow.com/users/505323/bruce) [Over a year ago](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/75817076/no-matter-what-i-do-podman-is-mounting-volumes-as-root#comment140090662_79216257)
  
  You can apply multiple volume mount options by comma separating them. To apply both SELinux relabelling and volume mount chowning use. `--volume /home/fred/pod-test/testvol:/mnt/testvol:Z,U` If the volume is to be shared among multiple containers replace the `Z` option with `z`.
  
